'''OpenOffice.org Math''' is a tool for creating and editing [[mathematical notation]], similar to [[Microsoft Equation Editor]] and is part of the [[OpenOffice.org]] [[office suite]]. The created formulae can then be embedded inside other OpenOffice.org documents, such as those created by Writer. It supports multiple [[font]]s and can export to [[Portable Document Format|PDF]].
Released under the terms of the [[GNU Lesser General Public License]], Math is [[free software]].
==See also== {{Portal|Free software}} * [[Comparison of office suites]] * [[MathMagic]] Stand-alone WYSIWYG equation editor.
